data.enText: to move, or make sb/sth move, around quickly in a circle or in a particular direction

data.chText: 她猛地转过身子面对着他。
data.enText: She whirled around to face him.
the whirling blades of the helicopter

data.chText: 汤姆拥着她从舞池的一边旋转到另一边。
data.enText: Tom whirled her across the dance floor.

data.chText: （头脑、思想等）混乱不清，激动，恍惚
data.enText: if your mind, thoughts, etc. whirl , you feel confused and excited and cannot think clearly

data.chText: 我睡不着，所发生的一切一直在脑子里转来转去。
data.enText: I couldn't sleep─my mind was whirling from all that had happened.

data.chText: 她思绪万千，脑子里乱作一团。
data.enText: So many thoughts whirled around in her mind.
a movement of sth spinning round and round
Her mind was in a whirl (= in a state of confusion or excitement) .

data.chText: 接连不断的活动；纷至沓来的事件
data.enText: a number of activities or events happening one after the other

data.chText: 她的生活就是接连不断的聚会。
data.enText: Her life was one long whirl of parties.

data.chText: 很容易被纷繁的社交活动缠得脱不开身。
data.enText: It's easy to get caught up in the social whirl .
to try sth to see if you like it or can do it

means: (头脑、思想等)混乱不清，激动，恍惚

ex.chText: 火星是每24小时绕轴线自转一周吗？
ex.enText: Does Mars rotate on its axis once every 24 hours?

ex.chText: 烘烤过程中不要忘记转动托盘。
ex.enText: Don't forget to rotate the pan throughout the baking time.

synonyms.bx: 指物体围绕自己的轴或中心旋转，在特定语境中指自转。

ex.enText: Seagulls circled around above the sea.

ex.chText: 飞机在机场上空盘旋，等待指挥塔的指令。
ex.enText: The plane circled the airport, waiting for the order from the control tower.

ex.chText: 那个轮子为什么不转了？
ex.enText: Why did that wheel stop revolving?

ex.chText: 怎样才能旋转屏幕上的图像？
ex.enText: How can I revolve the image on the screen?

ex.chText: 地球绕太阳公转是常识。
ex.enText: It is common sense that the earth revolves around the sun.

synonyms.bx: 指物体像轮子一样转动，在特定语境中指公转。

ex.chText: 飞机的螺旋桨在快速旋转时，要离得远一些。
ex.enText: Stay away when the plane's propellers are spinning.

ex.chText: 那位做旋转动作的溜冰者吸引了她的注意力。
ex.enText: The spinning ice skater attracted her attention.

synonyms.bx: 强调迅速、连续地旋转，多指绕轴心转动。

ex.chText: 看！海鸥在港口上空盘旋。
ex.enText: Look! The seagulls are whirling over the harbour.

ex.chText: 新郎抱着新娘转了起来。
ex.enText: The groom whirled the bride round in his arms.

synonyms.bx: 强调速度快，含飞旋之意。

data.enText: to try sth to see if you like it or can do it

example: he gave the crank a spin
it broke off after much twisting
he took a crack at it
he was caught up in a whirl of work
a commotion of people fought for the exits

tr: the shape of something rotating rapidly
revolve quickly and repeatedly around one's own axis
example: The dervishes whirl around and around without getting dizzy

tr: flow in a circular current, of liquids

example: The clothes tumbled in the dryer
rising smoke whirled in the air

tr: turn in a twisting or spinning motion
example: The leaves swirled in the autumn wind

value.def: If something or someone whirls around or if you whirl them around, they move around or turn around very quickly.

example.ex: Not receiving an answer, she whirled round...
example.tran: 没有得到答案，她飞快地转过身去。

example.ex: He was whirling Anne around the floor...
example.tran: 他正拉着安妮在舞池内转圈儿。

example.ex: The smoke began to whirl and grew into a monstrous column.
example.tran: 浓烟开始盘旋上升，形成了一个巨大的烟柱。
几乎听不见轮子的转动声

value.def: You can refer to a lot of intense activity as a whirl of activity.

example.ex: In half an hour's whirl of activity she does it all...
example.tran: 经过半个小时的忙碌，她全都做完了。

example.ex: Your life is such a social whirl.
example.tran: 你总是在不停地参加社交活动。

value.tran: 一连串;接连不断的活动

value.def: If a person or their mind is in a whirl, they are very confused or excited.

example.ex: My thoughts are in a whirl.

value.def: If you decide to give an activity a whirl, you do it even though it is something that you have never tried before.

example.ex: Why not give acupuncture a whirl?...
We decided to give it a whirl.
